The paper deals with algorithms for the closest vector problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and optimization. The paper also introduces a geometric covering problem, which is related to the closest vector problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI), so these categories are also likely.
